So...

So...


They're Anakim, right? Except they're (sorta) Jewish now. It's not really my area of study, so I'd have to do some solid Wikipedia diving to really suss out exactly what's going on here, but I'm certainly intrigued.

Something I thought was clever is that how travelling off-continent is  that is, everything you need to cross an ocean short of preserved food and a boat. What are they hiding?




I fixed the XXXXes for you, but there are a few apparent errors that I didn't feel confident unilaterally changing:

 Metric should be used here. A meter is just a bit longer than a yard, for reference.
 can't be right, unless it's some hot new system I've never heard of.
Political organization into nation-states is a very interesting choice, as it would be thoroughly anachronistic for a pseudo-Iron Age society  nation-states are a European invention that more-or-less superseded empires sometime between the 15th and 19th centuries, depending on who you ask. Noticeably, they've never coincided with egalitarian societies :^) If this oddity was deliberate, you can leave it in, but if the aim is realism I'd suggest some other political formation.
 is redundant. I'd recommend cutting the first two words.
